#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=Do you believe in a higher power ?
#Text=Yes I do .
#Text=I do n’t know what it is .
#Text=I just think its some higher form of energy and some sort of being , but I ca n’t embody it in my mind .
#Text=But I know I have a one to one , kind of a spiritual connection to whatever that is .
#Text=See I was raised , I had Catholicism shoved down my throat .
#Text=I was an altar boy .
#Text=I knew the mass in Latin .
#Text=Me too .
#Text=Really ?
#Text=I did n’t know the mass in Latin , but I was an altar boy and I had Catholicism shoved down my face , but I ’m 33 , so Vatican II had happened .
#Text=Yeah , and then you get " Father PreCum " trying to give you a massage and shit like that .
#Text=The priest at my church got a nun pregnant and my mother , who was the president of the PTA at my Catholic grade school , helped deliver the baby and keep the whole thing hidden .
#Text=Really ?
#Text=Yeah .
#Text=And he ’s still the priest .
#Text=I think it ’s probably a guy masquerading as a nun , if you ’re talking about priests .
#Text=West on his career
#Text=Where do you see yourself now in your career ?
#Text=Exactly where I want to be .
#Text=You know , I feel bad for kids who want to be voice-overs .
#Text=They will always be needed .
#Text=I always encourage them .
#Text=They ’re always going to need what you offer .
#Text=And you can make a living if you ’re really good .
#Text=But there ’s only so far you can go now .
#Text=Before , the sky was the limit .
#Text=There was n’t these rigged fights standing in your way . '
#Text=Cause right now , it ’s like a rigged fight .
#Text=You can still audition and get great satisfaction on the job as a voiceover .
#Text=And that ’s all I ever really wanted to be .
#Text=But I did aspire to do animations that required voice work .
#Text=And I ’ve done some of it and then this trend set in .
#Text=And believe me we do n’t get the kind of money those people get for doing voices .
#Text=It ’s rather odd to me .

#Text=At some point I realized many years ago — I was a teenager in the sixties , protesting with the long hair , running around with the hippies — I realized when I looked at all the guys we were supposed to hate so much and resent , I kind of analyzed what complacency was , and they seemed complacent to me .

#Text=They reached a point in their lives where they felt good about themselves and just cause a bunch of kids come along that were popping drugs and accusing you of this and that and being the man and everything , you think your feelings states are never going to change .
#Text=And I used to say they ’re complacent .
#Text=But the thing is that everybody that ’s born pretty much has to reach that point where they ’re looking down the barrel of their own complacency .
#Text=You gotta like do a little gear shifting .
